The Help Scout Model Context Protocol (MCP) server enables AI assistants to interact with your Help Scout account to search conversations, pull customer profiles, and retrieve thread histories. You can use it with any MCP-compatible client like Claude Desktop, Cursor, or VS Code [1][2][3].

To set it up, create a Private App in your Help Scout account settings to obtain your App ID and App Secret. Add the server to your MCP configuration file using the following structure:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "helpscout": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@gravitykit/help-scout-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "HELPSCOUT_APP_ID": "your-app-id",
        "HELPSCOUT_APP_SECRET": "your-app-secret"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This server supports features like PII redaction, automatic API rate limit handling, and advanced search filters for tickets and customers [1][2][3]. Note that Help Scout exclusively uses the OAuth2 Client Credentials flow for authentication [1][2].
